Crowd Mixer Community Edition — Licensing

This extension package (everything inside this "CrowdMixer" folder, i.e.
everything submitted to extensions.blender.org: the .py source files, the
UI icons/images under CMX_Icons/ and CMX_Images/, the geometry node
templates under GeometryNodes/, and the preset metadata/thumbnails under
CMX_Preset/) is licensed in full under the GNU General Public License,
version 3 or later. See LICENSE-CODE for the full license text.

This extension does not bundle any 3D character assets. Instead, it reads
a separate, user-supplied "Asset Path" (see the addon preferences) that
points at the CrowdMixer character/environment asset library
(CMX-Single-Mesh/, CMX-Source/, Object_Preset_Crowd/, distributed as
"CrowdMixer_Asset" outside of extensions.blender.org). That library is
licensed separately under its own custom content terms — see
LICENSE-ASSETS — since it is 3D models, textures and rigs rather than
software, and the GPL is written for the latter:
https://docs.blender.org/manual/en/dev/advanced/extensions/licenses.html

If you only use this extension as an end user inside Blender, you do not
need to do anything special — the GPL already permits that use, and the
separately obtained asset library comes with its own terms of use.
